OL,3,CRetail spending heats up in June due
OL,4,Cto warm weather ` BRC
OL,6,FThe BRC found that non-food sales
OL,7,Fincreased by 2.2% in June, with
OL,8,Fsimilar rates of growth across online
OL,9,Fand in stores.
OL,11,FHelen Dickinson, chief executive of
OL,12,Fthe BRC, said: "Retail sales heated up
OL,13,Fin June, with both food and non-food
OL,14,Fperforming well.
OL,16,F"The soaring temperatures increased
OL,17,Fsales of electric fans while sports
OL,18,Fand leisure equipment was boosted by
OL,19,Fboth the weather and the start of
OL,20,FWimbledon.
