OL,3,CRetail spending heats up in June due
OL,4,Cto warm weather ` BRC
OL,6,FIt, however, highlighted that sporting
OL,7,Fevents and festivals helped drive an
OL,8,Fuptick of non-essential spending, with
OL,9,Fentertainment, hotels and travel
OL,10,Fspending all higher.
OL,12,FThe figures also showed that furniture
OL,13,Fretailers saw a strong month, with an
OL,14,F8.2% increase in sales.
OL,16,FThe overall dip came despite surveyed
OL,17,Fcustomers indicating that their
OL,18,Fconfidence about their finances is at
OL,19,Fits strongest level for four months.
