OL,3,CRetail spending heats up in June due
OL,4,Cto warm weather ` BRC
OL,6,FKaren Johnson, head of retail at
OL,7,FBarclays, said: "Despite the warm
OL,8,Fweather, which usually boosts non-
OL,9,Fessential sectors such as retail and
OL,10,Fhospitality, consumers spent
OL,11,Fcautiously in June, prioritising value
OL,12,Fas they navigate economic uncertainty.
OL,14,F"Encouragingly, entertainment, beauty
OL,15,Fand furniture stores bucked the trend,
OL,16,Fwhile confidence in household finances
OL,17,Fimproved, showing consumers'
OL,18,Fwillingness to spend on the things
OL,19,Fthat matter most to them."
